Zanie  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kalinowo, within Ełk County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in north-eastern Poland. It is located in the region of Masuria. It lies approximately  north-east of Kalinowo,  north-east of Ełk, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
History
The village was founded in 1472.
During World War II, on December 5, 1943, a unit of the Polish Home Army captured a German post in the village, killing its commander and seizing weapons, ammunition and a dozen sets of uniforms.
Transport
The S61 highways bypasses Zanie in the south.
